Upstream speed = v - 3.6 mph
Downstream speed = v + 3.6 mph

Time upstream = 45/(v - 3.6) hours

Given that upstream trip takes 2.3 hours longer:
45/(v - 3.6) - 45/(v + 3.6) = 2.3

Multiplying through by (v - 3.6)(v + 3.6):
45(v + 3.6) - 45(v - 3.6) = 2.3(v - 3.6)(v + 3.6)

324 = 2.3v² - 29.808
2.3v² = 353.808
v² = 153.83826086956521739130434782609

question: A train leaves a station at 72 km/h. Two hours later, a faster train leaves the same station at 88.4 km/h. How long after the faster train departs will it overtake the slower one?
returned_answer:

Let t = time (in hours) after the faster train departs when it overtakes the slower train.

Distance traveled by slower train from when faster train starts: 72t km
Total distance of slower train: 144 + 72t km
Distance traveled by faster train: 88.4t km

When they meet: 88.4t = 144 + 72t
88.4t - 72t = 144
16.4t = 144
t = 144/16.4 = 8.78048780487804878048780487804878048780487804878048
